      <category><![CDATA[Shiba Inu]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://alltypesofdogs.org/?p=1231</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;All training is supposed to be fun and entertaining. If it isn&amp;#8217;t you won&amp;#8217;t like it, and your Shiba most certainly won&amp;#8217;t enjoy it. So grab the popcorn for you, treats for him and get ready to have some fun.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In this article we&amp;#8217;re going to teach our Shiba Inu the &amp;#8220;Down&amp;#8221; and &amp;#8220;Come&amp;#8221; commands. Keep in mind that he doesn&amp;#8217;t need to know sit and stay to learn down, but he needs to stay to learn come.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He doesn&amp;#8217;t need sit for down because [...] &lt;strong&gt;More about:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="http://alltypesofdogs.org/complete-your-shiba-inu-basic-obedience-training-with-down-and-come.html"&gt;Complete Your Shiba Inu Basic Obedience Training With &amp;#8220;Down&amp;#8221; and &amp;#8220;Come&amp;#8221;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/all-types-of-dogs-realm/All_Types_Of_Dogs_Realm-Complete_Your_Shiba_Inu_Basic_Obedience_Training_With_Down_and_Come.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
