      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://alltypesofdogs.org/?p=1218</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Training your Shiba Inu is instrumental in controlling him. The breed is very active and quite dominant. Your dog will mop the floor with you if you&amp;#8217;re not up to par. There are a few basic obedience commands which your dog must know. The first and most important is to teach him to focus his attention on you.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The &amp;#8220;Watch me&amp;#8221; command makes everything else seem like an evening walk. It&amp;#8217;s actually so useful for a Shiba Inu that most behavior problems are already solved [...] &lt;strong&gt;More about:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="http://alltypesofdogs.org/train-your-shiba-inu-to-respond-to-the-watch-me-command.html"&gt;Train Your Shiba Inu to Respond to the &amp;#8220;Watch Me&amp;#8221; Command&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/all-types-of-dogs-realm/All_Types_Of_Dogs_Realm-Train_Your_Shiba_Inu_to_Respond_to_the_Watch_Me_Command.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
