      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://alltypesofdogs.org/?p=1200</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We&amp;#8217;ve talked about teaching your Shiba Inu the Open Tunnel and how fun it is. The other type of tunnel found in agility courses is the collapsed tunnel. This tunnel is usually shorter and has a long cloth dangling over one end. Of course, you can always use a towel.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Before you attempt the collapsed tunnel you should master the open tunnel. It&amp;#8217;s important to do so because this one is a lot scarier and incorporates something most dogs detest, things touching their head.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It [...] &lt;strong&gt;More about:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="http://alltypesofdogs.org/teach-your-shiba-inu-the-collapsed-tunnel-is-cool.html"&gt;Teach Your Shiba Inu the Collapsed Tunnel is Cool&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/all-types-of-dogs-realm/All_Types_Of_Dogs_Realm-Teach_Your_Shiba_Inu_the_Collapsed_Tunnel_is_Cool.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
