      <description>&lt;p&gt;You&amp;#8217;ve set your foam board, cut it into the designed shapes and you have your hurdle ready. Now it&amp;#8217;s time to introduce your Shiba Inu to his new toy. The point of jumping hurdles isn&amp;#8217;t to jump as high as possible.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;If you&amp;#8217;re doing this in the living room, with no backyard access it&amp;#8217;s actually very dangerous to try full-height jumps. The fun is negotiating the timing of the jump and the approach. Your dog will have just as much fun jumping 1 inch, as [...] &lt;strong&gt;More about:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="http://alltypesofdogs.org/teach-your-shiba-inu-to-jump-the-hurdles.html"&gt;Teach Your Shiba Inu to Jump the Hurdles&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/all-types-of-dogs-realm/All_Types_Of_Dogs_Realm-Teach_Your_Shiba_Inu_to_Jump_the_Hurdles.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
