      <category><![CDATA[Shiba Inu]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://alltypesofdogs.org/?p=1176</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Shiba Inus are very active little dogs and you would expect they need lots of room to run amok. However, they are quite happy jumping off the couch and doing tricks in the house, though they need some additional exercise on top of that.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I think it&amp;#8217;s safe to say that all Shibas prefer walks to eating. You will find that your Shiba won&amp;#8217;t let you stay on the couch all day. They will nit-pick at your toes and whatnot, determined to get you off [...] &lt;strong&gt;More about:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="http://alltypesofdogs.org/playtime-exercise-and-training-with-a-shiba-inu.html"&gt;Playtime, Exercise and Training With a Shiba Inu&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/all-types-of-dogs-realm/All_Types_Of_Dogs_Realm-Playtime_Exercise_and_Training_With_a_Shiba_Inu.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
